[
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.1",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "When thou sittest to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what {is} before thee:",
    "hash": "63e69fcbe9a6e22837a97f9ccbaf30bf7179497da4934f8f8b44245a5ab17101"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.2",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And put a knife to thy throat, if thou {be} a man given to appetite.",
    "hash": "0e48ade7113a1474f8ca1687610a6455f6a8ef5a23f2baca12c55e1e686e60aa"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Be not desirous of his dainties: for they {are} deceitful meat.",
    "hash": "52394968ddf785fe3f77bdf570ba688270b6368fc8936e546319fdad53984248"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Labour not to be rich: cease from thine own wisdom.",
    "hash": "6e2670f059e858d9a86f361a05ba383c75082812d61ad2bf73d8a796b835dee9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.5",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not? for {riches} certainly make themselves wings; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven. {set...: Heb. cause thine eyes to fly upon}",
    "hash": "4d4686cb47f54431ebff806422a593943c4d36870d831f753f6ace2918c9b877"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.6",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Eat thou not the bread of {him that hath} an evil eye, neither desire thou his dainty meats:",
    "hash": "ae8fce9c720aa326436f5b1dc9aa24bd0ae5eff3425619e86b57d7a0acd6379c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.7",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For as he thinketh in his heart, so {is} he: Eat and drink, saith he to thee; but his heart {is} not with thee.",
    "hash": "d4682d535059a439920e4fa4044a29f61ddc422ee7da9e6be07657c5c95584c7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.8",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "The morsel {which} thou hast eaten shalt thou vomit up, and lose thy sweet words.",
    "hash": "bd68b3746f6b2c024f71afb81857be7a462d8b7effb4ef3a9874aa98b9c28636"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.9",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Speak not in the ears of a fool: for he will despise the wisdom of thy words.",
    "hash": "5e70da14092e7551a7bb366b4586943385e7903e126266e556484eb0d438bedb"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.10",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Remove not the old landmark; and enter not into the fields of the fatherless: {landmark: or, bound}",
    "hash": "6893726bd56d222f44abdd49015580f37061673b5b41fa2b0c11dc90cc758273"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.11",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "For their redeemer {is} mighty; he shall plead their cause with thee.",
    "hash": "ed1fecae2310b83dd9ab39d1c484acf5653649177d510751d5797627c6625cf1"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.12",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Apply thine heart unto instruction, and thine ears to the words of knowledge.",
    "hash": "6e89e4e22cf39f792fd2cb1ed48de72ef945be2009b59b2d70bd7e3d8ba29aca"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.13",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Withhold not correction from the child: for {if} thou beatest him with the rod, he shall not die.",
    "hash": "c9d6027d78a9694efe289713580862b7eeb9b170d409ce7e42cc6e8e3a2faf09"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.14",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from hell.",
    "hash": "9141ee8bb8a4fd6ded17576d7d4371df7b56942e0acb881889128bd775725044"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.15",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "My son, if thine heart be wise, my heart shall rejoice, even mine. {even...: or, even I will rejoice}",
    "hash": "7498c15531e1457161c986fb5b40bd2cdbba8ba5b4996162f289799d368c480e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.16",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Yea, my reins shall rejoice, when thy lips speak right things.",
    "hash": "ae938180818f1eb73def7e3606abf1774760293afbcab3ba4f182cd43dd946f7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.17",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Let not thine heart envy sinners: but {be thou} in the fear of the LORD all the day long.",
    "hash": "980f7b60dec96a39322a6e3791b62e167ebf191f147a841b31c2fcb859067803"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.18",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "For surely there is an end; and thine expectation shall not be cut off. {end: or, reward}",
    "hash": "cb71d64eada63f0c096059f6c99c5f43bb364d362d02a98742f80070dadc2c6f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.19",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Hear thou, my son, and be wise, and guide thine heart in the way.",
    "hash": "ccd258116d48bece04d2a584510fef7b726e86a1766581213d760b70dacb7662"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.20",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Be not among winebibbers; among riotous eaters of flesh: {of flesh: Heb. of their flesh}",
    "hash": "8d0791da75a3f292f43631c6f30663d00480c6a4fedee256a16988afffedab01"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.21",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty: and drowsiness shall clothe {a man} with rags.",
    "hash": "01274338f0d1bbdd0602c227bdee653dea7ffd497f980d682d3344086e67ada7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.22",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Hearken unto thy father that begat thee, and despise not thy mother when she is old.",
    "hash": "49519b9687cb6c48870d659b3a193feffe6213e4690d3ded38d4d354085b201e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.23",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Buy the truth, and sell {it} not; {also} wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.",
    "hash": "08ec062671ae2b67bd3bbcdac517eadaa843e12c50888981c883bd49c7b9907d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.24",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice: and he that begetteth a wise {child} shall have joy of him.",
    "hash": "628daca709502c6da48f67233cdb667b6e120e2a0fd676bd76744c03201ba74b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.25",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Thy father and thy mother shall be glad, and she that bare thee shall rejoice.",
    "hash": "0f96ea21085971164b87fd977720b80ab0c1cc965ca6d2ac5f90829defbbf865"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.26",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways.",
    "hash": "772778fd8afab38c943c9136d2e06d4ba42225b860c941337923b5e006104de0"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.27",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "For a whore {is} a deep ditch; and a strange woman {is} a narrow pit.",
    "hash": "fedf042127c33f901d45b7294dbb4e5fed9e298c1b29269b5234c085ad0309ae"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.28",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "She also lieth in wait as {for} a prey, and increaseth the transgressors among men. {as for...: or, as a robber}",
    "hash": "7d93de9d315044edeb925597516a1033511053693c26e1a3983f5cb6fa9dff71"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.29",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Who hath woe? who hath sorrow? who hath contentions? who hath babbling? who hath wounds without cause? who hath redness of eyes?",
    "hash": "08c642e2cde0bbe84a0ea9b7d1593786ed4df5e2cd88fbfd01e7e55f276ee6f3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.30",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "They that tarry long at the wine; they that go to seek mixed wine.",
    "hash": "1cff4e9c8702524be40504425a3d3ba005eabd9256823dfa21845697739306b9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.31",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Look not thou upon the wine when it is red, when it giveth his colour in the cup, {when} it moveth itself aright.",
    "hash": "b159496be52327397e4e462c2641ec40f6fea3f5df69cdf578c93008e9219ac3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.32",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "At the last it biteth like a serpent, and stingeth like an adder. {an...: or, a cockatrice}",
    "hash": "89cac260266a0b5c2654b291de323d01e1be3484a3e274b961a11af0a2bd5f54"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.33",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Thine eyes shall behold strange women, and thine heart shall utter perverse things.",
    "hash": "544d393ce34e2f7f5ba707b72d693dd33cb4ecaa24bc68adebc47be39fdb761f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.34",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down in the midst of the sea, or as he that lieth upon the top of a mast. {the midst...: Heb. the heart of the sea}",
    "hash": "e23b07f6bde7c2fbb40bd3123db3af0c0a884fe01db1d498c611a99cd9e7c06f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.23.35",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 23,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "They have stricken me, {shalt thou say, and} I was not sick; they have beaten me, {and} I felt {it} not: when shall I awake? I will seek it yet again. {I felt...: Heb. I knew it not}",
    "hash": "b9c2b9eed670a484d91e447c2511ec91cd56fc08bf48b2a2afc4b63560ea3f6f"
  }
]